excerpt: Long fishing pier offering pavilions, telescopes & a bait house with snacks, plus sunset views.
detail_description: Pier 60 is a popular fishing pier in Clearwater, offering pavilions, telescopes, and a bait house with snacks. Visitors can enjoy nightly sunset celebrations two hours before and after sunset, featuring local vendors, artists, and musicians. For just $1, you can explore the remaining 1,080 feet of the pier for recreational fishing with beautiful beach views.
name: Pier 60

excerpt: Laid-back Clearwater Beach is known for its namesake stretch of soft, white sand, which draws visitors year-round for jet-skiing, parasailing, and stand-up paddleboarding in its calm waters. Cyclists and rollerbladers glide along a winding beachfront promenade lined with casual seafood restaurants and cafes. Come sunset, Pier 60 hosts a nightly festival with street performers and craft vendors.
detail_description: Clearwater Beach is a laid-back destination famous for its soft, white sand and calm waters, perfect for activities like jet-skiing, parasailing, and paddleboarding. The beachfront promenade offers a scenic route for cyclists and rollerbladers with plenty of seafood restaurants and cafes to explore. As the sun sets, Pier 60 comes alive with nightly festivals featuring street performers and craft vendors.
name: Clearwater Beach

excerpt: Home of the inspiration for "Dolphin Tale," this aquarium exhibits marine mammals & sea turtles.
detail_description: Located in Clearwater Beach, the Clearwater Marine Aquarium is a renowned facility dedicated to rescuing, rehabilitating, and releasing marine animals. It was established in 1972 and is housed in a former water treatment plant with large pools ideal for rehabilitation operations. The aquarium is home to various injured marine life that cannot return to the wild. One of its most famous residents was Winter, a bottle-nosed dolphin whose story inspired the movie 'Dolphin Tale.'
name: Clearwater Marine Aquarium

excerpt: Island park with white sand beaches plus swimming, boating, fishing & picnic facilities.
detail_description: Caladesi Island State Park is a serene oasis just off Clearwater's coast, offering visitors an escape from the usual tourist hustle. This pristine island can only be reached by ferry or kayak, making it a hidden gem for those seeking tranquility. With its stunning white sand beaches, it's ideal for beachcombing and shelling enthusiasts eager to discover unique seashells along the shore.
name: Caladesi Island State Park

excerpt: Tranquil, oak-lined paths, educational walking tours, natural exhibits & educational kids' camps.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Clearwater, Moccasin Lake Nature Park is a serene escape that offers an enchanting blend of nature and education. Spanning over 50 acres, this hidden gem features tranquil oak-lined paths and diverse wildlife, including birds of prey and peacocks. Visitors can explore 1.5 miles of boardwalk trails that meander through lush forests, making it perfect for leisurely strolls or more challenging hikes with stunning views from elevated bluffs.
name: Moccasin Lake Nature Park
address: 2750 Park Trail Ln, Clearwater, FL 33759, USA

excerpt: Expansive white-sand beach offering plenty of room for picnics, surfing & other outdoor activities.
detail_description: Sand Key Park is a stunning waterfront destination in Clearwater, offering a long stretch of pristine white sand and clear water. It combines the beauty of the beach with park amenities such as a dog park, cabanas, and a playground. Despite its scenic beauty, it's less crowded than Clearwater Beach. Visitors can enjoy picnics, surfing, and other outdoor activities while taking in the local marine wildlife. The park also features a salt marsh area with benches for bird-watching and relaxation.
name: Sand Key Park

detail_description: Embark on an exciting adventure with Captain Memo’s Pirate Cruise, a thrilling experience for all ages. Step aboard the authentic pirate ship replica and set sail across Clearwater Bay and the Gulf of Mexico. The spirited crew leads passengers in treasure hunts, limbo dances, and games with water guns and hula hoops. With guaranteed dolphin sightings and possible glimpses of sharks, rays, and manatees, this two-hour sightseeing cruise offers fun activities for both adults and children since 1993.
name: Captain Memo’s Pirate Cruise
address: 25 Causeway Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

excerpt: Roomy, modern setting for a slate of music, comedy & Broadway shows, plus arts education.
detail_description: Ruth Eckerd Hall, located in Clearwater, is a spacious and contemporary concert venue that offers a diverse range of entertainment including music, comedy, and Broadway shows. The hall's design ensures an unobstructed view from every seat, providing an intimate and immersive experience for all guests. Known for hosting renowned musicians and electrifying concerts, it has become a go-to destination for live performances in the Tampa Bay area.
name: Ruth Eckerd Hall
address: 1111 McMullen Booth Rd, Clearwater, FL 33759, USA

excerpt: Known for the variety of shells on its shores, this park also offers swimming, fishing & hiking.
detail_description: Honeymoon Island State Park, located in Dunedin, is a barrier island known for its pristine four-mile white-sand beach and clear, calm waters. Visitors can enjoy swimming, fishing, and hiking while taking in the natural beauty of the virgin slash pine forest. The park offers amenities such as showers, restrooms, a cafe serving food and drinks, and rentals for bicycles, kayaks, beach chairs, and umbrellas.
name: Honeymoon Island State Park

detail_description: Spectrum Field is a small, intimate baseball stadium in Clearwater, Florida that is home to the local minor league team, the Clearwater Threshers. The stadium has an electrifying atmosphere and is particularly popular with Phillies fans during spring training sessions. Tickets for minor league baseball games tend to be cheaper than tickets for televised MLB matches.
name: BayCare Ballpark
address: 601 N, Old Coachman Rd., Clearwater, FL 33765, USA

detail_description: The Clearwater Ferry offers a convenient and enjoyable way to travel from Dunedin Marina to Clearwater Beach. Passengers can enjoy the scenic ride and may even spot dolphins along the way. The ferry also makes stops at locations like Coachman Park before heading straight to the beach. Travelers recommend bringing a towel for windy conditions, but overall find the experience affordable and free of holiday traffic and parking hassles. They also emphasize the importance of tipping the captain for their service.
name: Clearwater Ferry

detail_description: Nestled right across from Clearwater Beach Municipal Marina, this vibrant locale is a hub for all things boating and water-related. Just a stone's throw away from the lively Pier 60, famous for its enchanting sunset celebrations, visitors can indulge in an array of activities. The marina boasts stunning views and calm waters, making it an ideal spot for families with young children to explore. From fishing trips to dolphin tours and parasailing adventures, there's no shortage of excitement here!
name: Clearwater Beach Municipal Marina

detail_description: Jolley Trolley Transportation offers a convenient and scenic way to explore Clearwater Beach and the surrounding towns. The trolley operates along the coastal route, providing easy access to various attractions. Additionally, it is available for charter services for special events. Customers have praised the company for its excellent service during weddings and other occasions. With affordable fares for seniors and adults, Jolley Trolley provides a cost-effective transportation option compared to rideshare services like Uber or Lyft.
name: Jolley Trolley Transportation
address: 1230 S Myrtle Ave Suite 301, Clearwater, FL 33756, USA

excerpt: Upscale rooms, some with ocean views, plus a private beach, modern dining & an outdoor pool.
detail_description: The Sheraton Sand Key Resort offers upscale rooms, some with ocean views, and a private beach. Guests can enjoy modern dining options and an outdoor pool. Rustys Bistro at the resort is known for its Thanksgiving buffet featuring a variety of delectable dishes including Gulf favorites like cocktail shrimp, oysters, and crab claws. The carving station offers citrus-marinated turkey and other savory options. Additionally, there's a chef's fall dessert table with cakes, pies, cookies, and more.
name: Clearwater Beach Sheraton Resort on Sand Key
address: 1160 Gulf Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

excerpt: This serene state park with a sandy beach, nature trails & bayside mangrove forest draws kayakers.
detail_description: Caladesi Island is a serene state park with sandy beaches, nature trails, and a bayside mangrove forest that attracts kayakers. The Rotary Centennial Nature Center offers educational services on the park's history and natural resources. Accessible only by ferry from Honeymoon Island, this pristine island is a nature lover's paradise.
name: Caladesi Island

excerpt: Adventure-themed mini-golf course with waterfalls, gator feedings, scavenger hunts & arcade games.
detail_description: Located in Clearwater, FL, Congo River Golf is an adventure-themed mini golf course with waterfalls, gator feedings and scavenger hunts. The mini golf course is relatively difficult and has a cool Adventure theme.
name: Congo River Golf
address: 20060 US Hwy 19 N, Clearwater, FL 33764, USA

detail_description: The Ream Wilson Clearwater Trail, also known as the Clearwater East West Trail, is a long pathway that currently connects four parks and will eventually stretch from Tampa to the Gulf of Mexico in Florida. It is popular for biking and walking, with amenities such as new bathrooms, parking lots, playgrounds, tennis courts, and basketball courts along the way. The trail offers a separated path for various activities like walking, running, and rolling.
name: Ream Wilson Trail

detail_description: StarLite Cruises is a well-established family-owned business in Clearwater Beach, offering a diverse range of vessels to cater to different group sizes. With over 3 million satisfied customers since its inception in 1986, it has become one of the most trusted cruise operators in the region. The StarLite Majesty provides an elegant and exciting experience with its twin-decked entertainment venue, allowing guests to enjoy stunning coastal views while dining and dancing.
name: StarLite Cruises

detail_description: The Tropics Boat Tours at Clearwater Beach offers an exciting and educational experience for families. Their tropical-themed double-decker catamarans can accommodate up to 125 guests, providing excellent viewing opportunities for spotting dolphins, manatees, and sea turtles. The tours guarantee dolphin sightings and offer a fun-filled adventure with onboard guides pointing out these playful creatures. With various boat tours available, including the Dolphin Exploration Tour, visitors are promised an unforgettable experience exploring the beauty of the area.
name: The Tropics Boat Tours
address: 25 Causeway Blvd, Clearwater Beach, FL 33767, USA

excerpt: Stylish shopping center featuring boutiques for clothes & beachwear, plus bars & casual restaurants.
detail_description: Pelican Walk Plaza Clearwater Beach Florida is a mall with boutiques, restaurants, and bars. It's perfect for shoppers looking for something to do in Clearwater while they're on vacation.
name: Pelican Walk Plaza Clearwater Beach Florida
